See with eyes unclouded. -- Lady Eboshi and Ashitaka from Princess Mononoke</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ukagebu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kagebu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/28/01 5:49:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: manga bound?? </span><hr size=1> I didn't read much, and infact (none ^_^) But thats only because i don't like reading things that aren't in script format.<br>
<br>
I sueggest that you put it into a script before you try and make a manga out of it. It's more organized that paragraphs slapped together. Although you can't really express your writing talent by doing this, I find it's the best way to write.<br>
<br>
I'm writing my own script as well It's called &quot;Datenshi&quot; and if you make yours, please change the name if it's &quot;Immortality&quot;.<br>
<br>
script format is plain, simple, informative, and you can locate points and events that happen because of doublespacing<br>
<br>
example: (greusome) contains morbid violence<br>
<br>
*Scene 567 (why not): A rainy night, in a field*<br>
<br>
Anjo: &quot;...&quot;<br>
<br>
/Anjo stands in the field holding his sword. His enemy opposite to him brandishes a spear<br>
<br>
Furoki (grinning): &quot;... I'll break the silence then kid...&quot;<br>
<br>
/Anjo: &quot;Don't flatter yourelf by patrionizing me...&quot;<br>
<br>
Furoki (angered): &quot;You little BLEEP!&quot;<br>
<br>
/Furoki charges at anjo throwing his spear aimed at his neck.<br>
/Anjo quickly moves out the way and stabs Furoki in the gut<br>
<br>
Anjo: &quot;Die peacefully...&quot;<br>
<br>
/anjo quickly rips him apart with his sword from furoki's gut then to his head, killing him quickly. blood gushes yadda yadda yadda!<br>
<br>
Get my point.<br>
